1. NEVER pipe test output through `cat` or other commands that can potentially strip away the ANSI colors (i.e. don't use `cat` during any PyTest runs)

2. ALWAYS include these base flags:

   - `-vv` (double verbose for more detailed output)
   - `--log-cli-level=INFO`
   - `--asyncio-mode=auto` (for async tests)
   - `--capture=no` (to show all logs in real-time)
   - `PYTHONPATH=.` (for proper module imports)

3. Command Template:

   ```bash
   cd /path/to/workspace && PYTHONPATH=. pytest <test_path> -vv --log-cli-level=INFO --asyncio-mode=auto --capture=no
   ```

4. For single test execution, append the specific test case:
   ```bash
   cd /path/to/workspace && PYTHONPATH=. pytest <test_file>::<test_name> -vv --log-cli-level=INFO --asyncio-mode=auto --capture=no
   ```